<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4223] RocksDBStore should close all open iterators on close</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4223</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;RocksDBStore doesn&apos;t keep track of the open iterators. So when the store is closed due to rebalance or otherwise, this may result in resource leakage as any open iterators will not be closed.&lt;br/&gt;
The store should keep track of the open iterators and close them when the store is closed&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13007869">KAFKA-4223</key>
